<section class="animate-on-scroll">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <!-- Opening -->
    <blockquote class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-text leading-snug italic">
        "AI removed the bottleneck of writing code."
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-text-muted mt-4">
        Don't let testing become the new bottleneck.
      </p>
    </blockquote>

    <!-- The real problems -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
      <!-- Problem 1 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-warm border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">Speed creates risk</p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          AI lets you ship faster than ever. More code, more changes, more surface area.
          The faster you move, the more you need a <span class="text-text font-semibold">safety net</span>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 2 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-warm border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">No shared standard</p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Every developer prompts AI differently. One gets thorough tests, another gets superficial ones.
          There's no consistent bar for what <span class="text-text font-semibold">"well-tested" means</span>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 3 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-warm border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">Coverage isn't quality</p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          80% line coverage looks great in a report. But are those tests checking the right things?
          Are they catching security issues? <span class="text-text font-semibold">Edge cases? Regressions?</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 4 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-warm border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-text mb-2">No confidence signal</p>
        <p class="font-body text-base text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          "Is it safe to ship?" is still answered by <span class="text-text font-semibold">gut feel</span>,
          not data. You need a single, objective score that tells you where you stand.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Decorative divider -->
    <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 my-12">
      <span class="block h-px w-16 bg-border"></span>
      <span class="block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber"></span>
      <span class="block h-px w-16 bg-border"></span>
    </div>

    <!-- Transition -->
    <p class="font-body text-lg text-text-muted text-center leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      AI made writing tests <span class="text-text font-medium">essentially free</span>.
      The question isn't "should we test more?" &mdash; it's "why aren't we testing everything?"
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
